The paper discusses model-driven engineering, which is a subfield of software engineering (cs.SE). It specifically focuses on model transformations, which are a type of program that operates on models, making cs.PL (programming languages) another likely sub-category. The paper also introduces a type system for the domain-specific language used to represent model transformations, which falls under cs.LO (logic in computer science). Additionally, the paper discusses the correctness of generated models, which involves data management and verification, making cs.DB (databases) a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper's use of operational semantics and type systems suggests a connection to cs.AI (artificial intelligence) as well.
